Title: How can i dump the source of a php script in a frameset?
Question: In other words, what code does my browser see that i don't?
confused again.
Answer: PHP scripts are not processed by the browser - only HTML, XML and Javascript.

PHP is processed by the server, which then generates an HTML page which is output to a browser.

If you want to see the hidden stuff that your browser sees that you don't (cookies, http requests), 

<?

var_dump($_POST);
var_dump($_GET);
var_dump($_COOKIES);

or var_dump($_REQUEST);

?>

Title: Please help me to write a C++ program to find avg and std deviation?
Question: The question in detail is as follows
Define a class having a fixed array member variable size 10,and define member function for reading array values and finding the average and standard deviation
Answer: class C
{
public:
enum { NUM_VALUES = 10 };

private:
double m_values[NUM_VALUES];

public:
// Sets the number stored at index i in m_values to v
void SetValue(int i, double v) throw( std::exception )
{
if ( i < 0 || i >= NUM_VALUES ) throw std::exception("Index out of range");
m_values[i] = v;
}

// Gets the number stored at index i in m_values
double GetValue(int i) const throw( std::exception )
{
if ( i < 0 || i >= NUM_VALUES ) throw std::exception("Index out of range");
return m_values[i];
}

    // Returns the mean of the numbers stored in m_values
    double GetMean(void) const 
    {
        double sum = 0;
        for ( int i = 0; i < NUM_VALUES; i ++ ) sum += m_values[i];
        return sum / NUM_VALUES;
    }

    // Returns the sample standard deviation of the numbers stored in m_values
    double GetStandardDeviation(void) const 
    {
        double mean = GetMean();
        double sum = 0;
        for ( int i = 0; i < NUM_VALUES; i ++ ) sum += (m_values[i]-mean)*(m_values[i]-mean);
        return sqrt(sum/(NUM_VALUES-1));
    }
};
